
Please note as of this release, the 3.0 branch is now marked as 'stable'. 
The 2.2 branch will no longer be maintained.

This is the current release version of the 'stable' tree of ircd-ratbox.

If you are upgrading from 3.0.x, please read doc/whats-new-3.1.txt
If you are upgrading from 2.2, you must read doc/whats-new-3.0.txt
If you are upgrading from 2.1, you must read doc/whats-new-2.2.txt
If you are upgrading from 2.0, you must also read doc/whats-new-2.1.txt
If you are upgrading from 1.x, you must also read doc/whats-new-2.0.txt

-- ircd-ratbox-3.1.0-rc1
- The name of the executable that is generated is now ircd-ratbox 
  instead of ircd.  Any crontabs should be updated to reflect this change.  
  Also you should remove any old executables in the $PREFIX/bin directory
  named ircd, the install process will not do this for you.
- Built in DNS RBL support via the blocklist {} configuration option
- Add ipv6_tun_remap option. This remap transitional IPv6 technologies(teredo,
  6to4) to their IPv4 addresses for the purpose of channel bans and klines
- Nicklen is now a runtime configurable option(up to 30 characters)
  Nicklens beyond 30 will need a recompile as before.
- Minimum nickname length is settable as well with serverinfo::nicklen_min
- Add options to configure TLS versions and ECDH support as well. 
- WHOWAS history length can now be set at runtime with the whowas_length
  option
- CERTFP support for connect {}, operator {} and auth{}.  CERTFP acts as an
  additional gate to these blocks and does not replace password/challenge.
- Improve memory usage reporting
- The code is much more reliant on C99 features, gcc 4.x and clang have
  been tested.  Let us know if another compiler does not compile it.
- Fix time_t issues on 32bit OpenBSD with 64bit time_t
- General code cleanups, dead code removal
- REHASH memory leaks are gone!
- Add ELIST new ELIST features C and T
- TESTRBL <ip>: oper-only spot-check of a single IPv4 or IPv6 address
  against every configured blacklist{} zone. Reports per-zone HIT,
  MISS, CLEAN (NXDOMAIN), ERROR, or TIMEOUT without affecting any
  client and without modifying the issuing oper's connection state.
  /HELP TESTRBL describes the output.
- STATS n / STATS N (oper-only): per-zone DNSBL counters. One line per
  configured blacklist{} of the form
      n <zone> queries=N matches=N misses=N
  /HELP STATS now lists the letter.
- blocklist { } accepted as an alias for blacklist { } in ircd.conf
- map_oper_only=no combined with serverhide::flatten_links=yes now
  emits a config-load warning, since flatten_links overrides the
  intended /MAP visibility for non-opers.
- rblquery_t.queryid widened from uint16_t to uint32_t. The DNS
  helper IDs are 32-bit; truncation caused queryid mismatches and
  use-after-free on disconnect after roughly 65k lookups.
- IPv6 client lookups: rbl_isv6() returns the bit flag (0x2), so the
  previous "!= true" comparison made every IPv6 client skip every
  blacklist. Replaced with a proper truthiness check.
- rbl->refcount is now bumped before lookup_hostname() to handle
  synchronous failed_resolver callbacks safely.
- rbl_destroy()/rbl_clear_rbllists() ordering corrected to avoid a
  stale rb_dlinkDelete on previously-removed list entries during a
  REHASH while DNS lookups are in flight.
- TLS 1.3 NewSessionTicket suppression on server contexts. The
  existing SSL_OP_NO_TICKET flag only covered pre-1.3 stateless
  tickets; SSL_CTX_set_num_tickets(0) is now also called when built
  against OpenSSL 1.1.1 or newer (skipped for LibreSSL). Works around
  stalls observed against ircds linked to early OpenSSL 1.1.1
  patchlevels with known TLS-1.3 NST/post-handshake races.
- Raw ERR_error_string format string is no longer leaked into the
  user-facing SSL quit message.
- resolver/res.c proc_answer() now bounds-checks rd_length against
  the end of the packet buffer, fixing a 4- to 16-byte over-read on
  crafted T_A/T_AAAA/T_CNAME responses.
- parse_netmask() in src/hostmask.c clamps negative CIDR bit counts
  to zero, fixing a UB shift count when /-N appeared in DLINE/KLINE/
  TESTLINE input or in the config file.
- serverinfo::nicklen now clamps to NICKLEN-1 on overflow and to a
  sensible minimum on underflow instead of writing the raw configured
  value into ServerInfo.nicklen, where it could overflow stack/heap
  nick buffers in mr_nick / m_nick / set_initial_nick.
- bandb_handle_ban() validates parc before dereferencing parv[]
  entries
- linebuf chop-trailing loop guarded against size_t underflow on
  pathological inputs.
- failed_resolver callback is now deferred to the next event loop
  iteration to avoid use-after-free across the dns / s_auth boundary.
- AWAY message updates (changing an existing away string, not just
  toggling on/off) are now propagated to peer servers; the previous
  code only sent the on/off transition.
- Accept callback no longer fires on a closed fd after rb_set_nb()
  failure on the newly-accepted socket.
- call_hook() iterates with RB_DLINK_FOREACH_SAFE so a hook callback
  that removes itself does not corrupt the iteration.
- motd_path is preserved across REHASH when the new config omits it,
  matching the long-standing behaviour of other path settings.
- free_cachefile() no longer leaks the dlink_node for empty MOTD/help
  lines.
- scache_remove() is now called when a server departs, fixing an
  unbounded heap growth on burst/split-rejoin storms.
- YESNO command-line option handling no longer writes through a
  wrong-typed pointer and clobbers neighbouring globals.
- ipv6_tun_remap matching restored after a regression that disabled
  ban matching against the remapped IPv4 address; garbage rewrite of
  the underlying IPv4 sockaddr was also removed.


